This paper discusses privacy implications in web databases and proposes techniques to infer private attributes based on ranking functions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
